<li>Lead all regional operational activities across logistics, warehousing, inventory management, plant production, fleet management, procurement, and compliance functions for the KwaZulu-Natal branch.</li>
<li>Directly manage a team of up to 15 employees — including logistics personnel, plant operators, gas fillers, and warehouse staff — overseeing recruitment, onboarding, training, performance management, disciplinary processes, attendance control, leave management, and workforce scheduling.</li>
<li>Manage a fleet of 8 delivery vehicles, coordinating daily route planning and delivery schedules based on customer demand, stock availability, and operational priorities while ensuring optimal fleet utilisation.</li>
<li>Oversee vehicle maintenance, roadworthiness compliance, and DEKRA inspections, coordinating repairs with suppliers and service providers to ensure continuous operational readiness and legal compliance.</li>
<li>Maintain accountability for over 3,200 gas cylinders and high-value assets, conducting detailed stock investigations, variance analysis, asset tracking, and reconciliation to ensure complete inventory accuracy.</li>
<li>Administer stock control processes through Sage 200 Evolution, including inventory management, asset barcoding, stock allocations, Inter-Branch Transfers (IBTs), stock movements, and monthly stock reconciliations.</li>
<li>Investigate and resolve cylinder discrepancies, losses, damaged assets, and non-conforming stock, ensuring full traceability and compliance with company procedures.</li>
<li>Manage cylinder quarantine, testing, recertification, and condemnation processes, ensuring all defective or damaged cylinders are processed and transferred according to company and regulatory requirements.</li>
<li>Oversee production operations within the filling plant, ensuring achievement of daily production targets averaging approximately 250 cylinders per day while maintaining productivity, quality, and safety standards.</li>
<li>Perform final verification and sign-off of production batches, ensuring accuracy of cylinder testing, pressure readings, quality checks, and food-grade gas compliance requirements.</li>
<li>Procure and manage bulk LPG, CO2, helium, industrial gases, cylinders, PPE, and operational consumables, maintaining uninterrupted supply to support production and customer demand.</li>
<li>Develop and maintain supplier relationships, negotiate pricing structures, monitor supplier performance, and manage lead times to optimise operational efficiency and cost control.</li>
<li>Establish and manage operational budgets for plant consumables and operational requirements while monitoring inventory value, stock losses, and overall operational expenditure.</li>
<li>Act as the branch Health and Safety Representative, conducting regular safety inspections, risk assessments, toolbox talks, incident investigations, and compliance audits within a high-risk HazChem environment.</li>
<li>Ensure compliance with Department of Labour regulations, HazChem requirements, company safety standards, and customer audit requirements through effective documentation management and procedural control.</li>
<li class="highlight">🏆 Successfully led the branch through a Coca-Cola compliance audit with zero major findings — becoming the first branch within the organisation to achieve this result.</li>
<li>Monitor operational KPIs, fleet utilisation, inventory performance, stock movement trends, and production metrics, preparing detailed weekly and monthly management reports.</li>
<li>Utilise Sage 200 Evolution, TrackAbout, and Mix Telematics systems to manage inventory, fleet tracking, operational reporting, asset control, and performance monitoring.</li>
<li>Collaborate closely with sales, logistics, warehouse, and senior management teams to forecast stock requirements, improve operational planning, and ensure seamless service delivery across the region.</li>
<li>Exercise full operational decision-making authority within the branch, reporting directly to senior management and ensuring the effective execution of all regional operational objectives.</li>
</ul>
